    {
        "user": "UMQ6LR9NZ",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1771470168.059899",
        "client_msg_id": "C212C38B-5D8F-497E-A1DA-C2D3DC8E6B8D",
        "text": "Semantics of lua, with the expressive options of a Perl mixed with a JavaScript mixed with a vector oriented programming language like K or APL. \n\nI think the fellow who makes it is a K programmer. I know he's implemented a few variants of K in the past. \n\nI like it, mostly, though, because it's leeetle and learnable, while allowing you to do things in a few different ways. \n\nYou can just as easily write functional-first code as you can write imperative code as you can write vector-flavored code — and then you can mix and match as makes sense.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
